@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Block Quote";
    ViewData["DemoNumber"] = 25;
}
<div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-2xl px-4 py-6 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[260px_1fr]">
        <partial name="Demos/_DemoLayout" />
        <div>
            <div class="demo-card">
                <div class="demo-card-header">Block Quote</div>
                <div class="demo-card-body">
                    <p class="demo-description">Wrap selected text in a blockquote element to visually distinguish quotations, excerpts, and callouts from the surrounding content. Blockquotes can be nested for multi-level citations.</p>

                    <richtextbox
                        id="blockquoteEditor"
                        name="blockquoteEditor"
                        toolbar="{insertblockquote,indent,outdent}|{bold,italic}|{undo,redo}"
                        width="100%"
                        height="300px"
                        html="<h2>On the Value of Simplicity</h2><p>Great thinkers across centuries have returned to the same idea: clarity and simplicity are not limitations but strengths. In design, in writing, and in engineering, removing the unnecessary reveals what truly matters.</p><blockquote><p><em>Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication.</em></p><p>&mdash; Leonardo da Vinci</p></blockquote><p>This principle applies directly to software development. A clean interface with fewer controls often outperforms a crowded one, because users can find what they need without hesitation.</p><blockquote><p><em>Perfection is achieved, not when there is nothing more to add, but when there is nothing left to take away.</em></p><p>&mdash; Antoine de Saint-Exup&eacute;ry</p></blockquote><p>When building rich text editors, consider which formatting tools your users actually need. A focused toolbar is almost always better than an exhaustive one.</p>"></richtextbox>

                    <div class="demo-note">
                        <div class="demo-note-content">
                            <div class="demo-note-title">Note</div>
                            <p class="demo-note-text">Block quotes are rendered as HTML blockquote elements. Nest quotes by applying the blockquote command multiple times.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="code-panel">
                        <pre><code>&lt;richtextbox
    name="blockquoteEditor"
    toolbar="{insertblockquote,indent,outdent}|{bold,italic}|{undo,redo}"
    height="300px"
    html="..." /&gt;</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
